            "section": "",
            "ref_spans": []
        },
        {
            "text": "Despite most of the ophthalmological practice may be deferred, sometimes it is not possible to distinguish a true emergency without the SLE evaluation. While telemedicine represents a viable option in other medical specialties, ophthalmology represents a real challenge since it relies mainly upon a detailed SLE. Since no vaccine or effective antiviral currently exists, we only have universal public health measures to avoid disease spreading. Meanwhile, ophthalmologists, due to the proximity required to adequately evaluate our patients, are urged to take extreme caution aiming to contain COVID-19.",
